body:
packed structs and packed unions as a whole can either be signed or
unsigned. This information is used when it is used as a primary in an
expression, i.e. without accessing any of the members. E.g.

```systemverilog
struct packed signed {
  logic [15:0] x;
} signed_struct;
```

Add support for parsing and elaborating signed structs as well as a test that verifies that signed structs work as expected.

